title: For Sale:  Barrett & SCAR? Help Police this site from FAKE Sellers
postcontent: ArmsList'ers Unite! I'm tired of seeing $10,000 Barrett Rifles with $2500 scopes listed for $3500 with NO CITY, and a price so under valued that only an idiot would be suckered by it. Or $4000 SCAR with ACOG pics listed for $2400, NO CITY but they're happy to ship to your FFL... Right. You tell them you're in Jax, they say they're in Key West but can ship, you tell them you're actually on your way to the keys today, they say they're on a boat to Cuba but their wife can ship to your FFL. You say you're in Miami and they say they're in Jax or Clearwater. Any BS story to avoid Face to Face deals.These scammers need to be FLAGGED and IP/email info turned over to LEO's, hackers, mobsters, goombahs, nerds, triads, snake people, good ol boys, or anyone willing to deal out some "mercenary sensibility and lead pipe cruelty" on these low life scum bags.   Have a nice day... Seriously, as a community of Firearms traders and collectors, protect each other. Any and EVERY time you see a listing without a City, or a too good to be true price... FLAG the F-ers as SCAM. Let's make operating scams on armslist near impossible by keeping the less street smart buyers from getting screwed, and make these types of listings get flagged so fast that it's no longer worth their time and these jerkoffs go back to their Spamming Campaigns from a Nigerian Prince, or selling knockoff Sham-Wow's.The community has spoken, get the hell off our site, dirtbags.I hope we catch you in a parking lot, for a "spirited discussion" & the next time I run into you, I hope I'm driving. ArmsList'ers.... Take time out every time to FLAG these jerks out of business and off our site.MAGA: Making ArmsList Great Again takes action. MAKE it happen.I'm unregistered, but I'm "EliasDeSapier" on geemail from Tampa/St.Pete, and I've purchased from several on this site without any problems because I only ever deal FACE 2 FACE &'therefore have never been screwed. Never do mail deals, even to FFL, it could be a fake. If you want an FFL deal that bad, go buy direct/new, that extra $50-$100 is fraud insurance. For everything else, F2F in a public place. Stepping off my soap box, but feel free to send me support emails or call me out if you disagree. I'm just trying to keep this community as it should be, a "self regulated militia" of the people, by the people, for the people, & F the scammers!8:30pm UPDATE: First support email came in from "Roger" who also wants to remind everyone to quit asking, "Is XXXX still available?" ...because no ArmsList'er wants to receive junk mail all day, so we pull our listings once sold. title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare Llama IV
postcontent: I am listing a hard to find piece of Spanish firearms history, the Llama IV in 9mm or 38, with matching numbers.The gun is in fair condition. It is evident that at one point in time there was some slight surface rust, but the gun has been reblued and is currently rust free. The original grips are missing and have been replaced with some custom (more than likely homemade) target grips. The stampings are light but still visible.The Llama functions well, I test fired it with 50rds of light 38 super loads (well within the firearms original designated chamber pressures) with no apparent failures. The safety is functional, and the gun is a good copy of a 1911, sans grip safety.The model IV was the first gun produced by Llama and were not produced for the American market. The caliber is 9mm largo or 38 acp. The 38 acp is the exact same dimensionally as the 38 super auto, albeit the 38 acp is lower powered than the super. With light 38 super loads, the gun functions marvelously and all internals, including the bore, are in very good shape. It has a 5 1/2” barrel, slightly longer than a standard 1911. Production of the Llama IV started in 1932, with this specific firearm being produced in 1941. If any reference material is needed on this firearm, please email me and I will forward you to where I have found all of my information. I can also send more pictures if needed. These are extremely scarce on the American market, and it is truly a collectible that you will not find anywhere else.Asking price is $700 obo, willing to meet relatively close to Salisbury, NC.Open to any trade offers. Looking for 9mm carbines of good quality, AKs, ARs, big bore revolvers, old revolvers, military firearms... really any decent offer will be considered.
